You have been warned.  This game runs very terribly on my Nexus 4 despite the graphics not being very good. I can play most high end games btw.  It's not noticeable on the first couple of levels since they are small. But the later levels are larger and get very choppy and are next to unplayable. You CANNOT adjust the graphics settings either.  Let's talk about the next issue, the controls. Even using my MOGA Pro this game is very hard to control. It's hard to describe without experiencing it first hand which is why I suggest playing the free version.  Let me get this straight. I was not expecting Tony Hawk quality. But this is just a very bad game that doesn't even get the basics right. To make matters worse, you can't even play all the levels on the paid version. That's right you have to pay to get the last levels on top of already paying for the game.  Wait for a sequel and hope the developer learns from their mistakes.

Gonna give this game the credit for keeping me entertained for some time. The sound is OK, graphics are beautiful, really brings me back the good'ol days of Tony Hawk's Pro Skater on my PSX. However, the only reason I can't give this game a 5* rating is because of the gameplay. I mean, the character turns way too quickly, it's like an oval turn instead of a rounded turn. That affects precision while performing anything. It gets to be annoying, I still didn't get used to it. Could the developer please provide a fix? Or is it that I'm missing in game that can fix this issue? Keep up the great work guys, I think this game has potential for multiplayer and for a DLC campaign, even if that extra costs me some bucks, I'm willing to pay for it!

One of the greatest skateboarding games I've ever played and the android game I get more fun. At first, controls seems a little too hard, but once you get used to it, you'll only get better and better and also addicted.   It's a shame that it's a little short. I ended up all four "included" locations (also all objectives) in few hours. It could be explored more, with more levels and stuff. Maybe harder locations and objectives (additionally to the really nice ones you've created) with longest sessions.   The extra level with an additional charge is unnecessary and may sound a little bad for players that bought the game. You could charge a little more for the market app and include the extra level, or making it available to buy with experience points or something like that.  Really hope you keep up the development, being with updates that increases content in this version or a newer game version. I would easily pay for more of your games.
